  "text": "Calculation of the displacement induced phase change in the interferometer was achieved using temporal phase stepping, implemented by wavelength modulation via adjustment of the laser diode control current. The current controller was activated externally using a NI 9263 analogue output module in a NI cDAQ-9174 data acquisition chassis. The five-step algorithm [CITATION_1] was chosen for phase calculation which involves recording a series of five images with a relative phase difference of π/2. The optical frequency shift required to produce a π/2 phase shift with a 5 cm pathlength imbalance is 1.5 GHz, from equation (1) . The change in control current required to achieve this was calibrated by recording an initial image and then incrementing the current. Subsequent recorded images were subtracted from the initial image and a 2π phase shift was determined when the mean intensity of the subtracted image reached a minimum [CITATION_2] . The algorithm is applied to the series of images recorded both before and after deformation and the phase of each is calculated using the equation ",
